{
  "text": "Salmonella were detected only in pond 3 V. cholerae was not found in any sample for both prawn and water sample. However, a few researchers reported that they have detected V. cholerae in fresh water shrimp farms and some of the researchers has reported only the genus of the Vibrio, not the species, someone found many other Vibrios other than V. cholerae [CITATION_1] . Since cow dung was used for pond preparation and cow dung and poultry faeces was used as manure in pond 3 and 5, the total bacterial load, total coliforms and faecal coliform were higher in those ponds and may be the source of Salmonella [CITATION_2] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
